                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18220911-314-off1643 t18220911-314-crimeloc1645"></join>; the prisoner slept in the same bed two nights with me. On the 19th of September I got up and left him in bed, and my coat was hanging in the room. I returned about eight o'clock and met him coming down stairs; he came out of the back kitchen and said he had just got up; he sat down by me at breakfast. I went up stairs, missed the coat, came down directly and saw him going out; I told him to wait a moment; he returned and sat down. I said he must know something of it; he denied it, and just as the constable was coming, he said he had it on; it was found under his shirt next to his skin; he was distressed.</p>
